 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utuene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/01 10:04:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DOT's and stacking</span><hr size=1> <br>
One fire dot (Flame lick, immo, breath of ro)<br>
<br>
Winged death (wierd stacking, heard rumors of why VI did this but nothing official)<br>
<br>
One of the swarm line (Drifting Death, creeping crud, drones, stinging swarm).<br>
<br>
My recommendation is to use Winged or drifting death (dependant on level), stack it with Drones from ES vambs, and be done with it.<br>
<br>
Granted, if you have RFS you can likely stick Immo with consistancy, but without it stay away from the fire debuff / dot, resisted too often makes it extremely mana inefficient as compared to the MR swarm lines.<br>
<br>
Tuene<br>
Sol Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/01 12:47:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DOTs and stacking</span><hr size=1> Druids have 4 lines of dots.<br>
<br>
- Flame Lick / Immolate<br>
- Stinging Swarm / Drones of Doom / Creeping Crud / Drifting Death<br>
- Breath of Ro<br>
- Winged Death<br>
<br>
The epic effect, Nature's Wrath, stacks with all 4 lines, bringing the grand total to 5 for some lucky druids.<br>
<br>
-Quelm, 52 wanderer<br>
Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A> at: 4/9/01 1:51:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utetriancorbec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tetrian corbec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/01 4:15:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DOTs and stacking</span><hr size=1> easy way to find out, also the only way you can make sure people arent just letting out garbage is to try stacking them on yourself, then you can see the icons for your self, and witch ones that stacks.<br>
<br>
also you get a good feel on from your own health bar on how fast you can deal damage with dots.<br>
<br>
Do it in the arena, you dont loose exp in there, not even from an npc or falling damage.<br>
<br>
........<br>
<br>
at 53 you can stack 4 dots (if you dont have the epic)<br>
<br>
Winged death 1200  <br>
drifting death 600  <br>
immolate      300<br>
breath of ro  900<br>
<br>
all in all you can do around 3000 damage in 1 min, with all your dots stacked.<br>
<br>
thats over 10 ticks, so you deal around 300damage per tick (1tick=6sec)<br>
<br>
not very effecient, but its possible.<br>
<br>
effecient=only winged death, for a little extra speed use winged and breath of ro.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
Tet. <p><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/71/1522171.bmp>
