</i>
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umulerin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mulerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/01 6:59:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DOT's and stacking</span><hr size=1> I agree with Tetrian completely.  Only thing I would change is instead of winged and breath for extra speed, use winged and drifting...I hate the resists/fizzles on breath of ro, blows more mana than it's worth IMO.<br>
<br>
Mulerin Wulfkin<br>
60th on Karana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugorgodarkfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GorgoDarkfyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/10/01 4:11:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DOT's and stacking</span><hr size=1> Use Winged Death and ES Arms... a tad slower, but much more mana efficient :)<br>
